      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OUR ULTIMATE BONNY (1) was in the money at this track two runs ago before making up some ground but never threatening at her latest appearance over 1760m at Coolamon. No excuses from this advantageous draw. Tackles a similar assignment and she can give this a mighty shake. TIGERNATOR (8) settled in the leading division the went to the front and closed the race off well to win for the second time in a row last start over 1770m at this track, getting there by 5.5 metres. Gets a soft run on the inside of the second line but may need luck at some point. Leading hope based on recent form. MAJORS CREEK (4) is better than her last-start run for seventh over 1760m at Coolamon would suggest. Can place. ROCKET BOY (5) is in the mix following a fourth at his most recent appearance over 1710m at Goulburn.",
